skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:title: {"id": "aed124d7-2d19-42f5-9440-2dd6b895bfab", "value": "FISH Maritime Cargo Types Thesaurus"}
skos:ConceptScheme.dcterms:description: {"id": "8d566065-a478-403b-adb0-0d1bb236998b", "value": "Used to record the type of cargo being carried by a vessel on its final voyage and often found in association with the wreck site."}

skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "b2ede9d8-51b2-4650-b0b7-e194e237483e", "value": "Bells used either as a percussion instrument or for other purposes such as calling attention, marking time periods etc."}
{"id": "701a7d61-122f-4b87-8cbb-4357c619de35", "value": "Pipes manufactured from concrete used in the construction industry for drainage etc."}
{"id": "de6d44dd-c9cc-4b69-a9d2-3ec1114a2d9e", "value": "Hollow cylinders or tubes of ceramic, wood, plastic or metal used to convey liquids, gases etc. Used in a variety of industries."}
{"id": "7326ebbf-48c5-4a66-a147-cc9f827335e7", "value": "Pipes manufactured from iron and used for a variety of purposes."}
{"id": "79eecdd7-8df5-457d-ba24-96e1b7485016", "value": "Pipes manufactured from copper used for a variety of purposes, especially plumbing."}
{"id": "9b3c27d3-f32a-41cb-bcd9-6d30a01dc879", "value": "An odourless, tasteless powder obtained from cereals and potatoes, used for stiffening fabric."}
{"id": "5df46f20-7588-41ee-a7af-f0f82890eb18", "value": "Items worn or carried as an adjunct to clothing, for example, headdresses, sashes, fans, masks etc."}
{"id": "8b69892a-db89-4edf-a421-fc4a4a8c5015", "value": "Manufactured objects and devices used to apply a force to an object or perform a particular mechanical function."}
{"id": "e41ff519-5eb3-4d54-8df6-28569c6b3af8", "value": "Transportation, usually wheeled or tracked, used for the conveyance of goods or people."}

{"id": "20657971-ef2c-4734-b66a-9bc4b892e01b", "value": "A series of links joined together to form something that is flexible and strong. Usually metal, chains have a variety of uses but usually involve joining one item to another."}
{"id": "ad7aa931-48bd-478b-a7c6-f98a1d081662", "value": "Optical and/or navigational instruments with powerful lenses for observing remote objects or used in astronomy."}
{"id": "05c8bd88-9952-40e3-aeed-f203eda25a88", "value": "Equipment including diving suits, wet suits, oxygen tanks etc. used to enable people to undertake underwater activities."}
{"id": "cc0c03f9-9a1b-4660-83d3-36b43333605f", "value": "Explosive devices which produce spectacular visual effects when ignited."}

{"id": "1c5e38b2-05d2-4576-bfe2-e2bcb7252728", "value": "Writing implements; formerly quill pens made of bird feathers, and in more modern times fountain pens made of various materials with metal nibs, both used with ink to write."}
{"id": "da7d063d-89f2-4760-b86c-60f11d2da4ea", "value": "Goods, including portable objects and furniture, commonly found in the home."}
{"id": "074746aa-618b-4869-b2f5-322975d3ea7f", "value": "Articles, particularly drinking vessels, manufactured from glass."}

{"id": "d57f8ffd-df63-4404-ab65-cca70aea91ea", "value": "Any unspecified items without utility or function and prized for personal or domestic decorative value. Examples might be unspecified metal objects from the Bronze Age or Victorian Staffordshire china dogs."}
{"id": "de84ef44-7317-488c-9fb5-1bcfb6605db5", "value": "Objects designed to be played with, often a model or miniature replica of something and especially for a child."}

{"id": "0d5e1544-1dc3-47ec-9ba0-bfddff744953", "value": "Protective equipment, usually made of metal, to protect parts of the body, e.g. helmets, breastplates, or full suits of armour, to protect troops or individuals in warfare. Most examples date from the Middle Ages, obsolete from the 17th century."}
{"id": "cd5d8a2f-c710-48f4-b537-e0d472a99113", "value": "A liquid used to provide a protective or decorative cover to a surface."}
{"id": "0d8f5293-7ad7-4ca9-9909-bc92ddd98260", "value": "Equipment used to catch fish"}

{"id": "dfefb37e-7e1d-4d59-a63b-e7d522c15fe3", "value": "Personal apparatus for telling the time, worn either as jewellery or purely functional in nature, usually on the wrist or as a suspended fob."}
{"id": "21c24ceb-2b03-46d2-aa24-fea1fadf78a0", "value": "A substance designed to emit a sweet smell."}

{"id": "97747e63-6886-4c2c-b713-b16fdf7ad981", "value": "Line, cord or thread, especially that used for tying up parcels, etc. Also use for \"twine\", i.e. twisted thread, for the same purpose, and medieval equivalents, e.g. \"packthread\"."}

{"id": "057d1f38-d0f8-4ad6-bc55-249a2f6cda2e", "value": "Preparations for beautifying or enhancing the body, face, hair or skin, e.g. creams, and coloured \"make-up\" items, e.g. rouge, lipstick, etc."}
{"id": "ae41fc3a-9b0f-437e-931d-45cf70810a37", "value": "Buoys used to direct craft on water along the correct route or away from a hazard. Usually used in coastal areas."}
{"id": "73a54f75-a917-44a9-96ea-ad99621fd79b", "value": "Intended for personal decoration, objects made of precious, semi-precious or imitation metals and gemstones."}
{"id": "0916db1c-bb4e-4d06-a2b6-c6e7722db81f", "value": "Apparatus used for applying a mechanical force, or to perform a particular function. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "1e12e292-5907-41dd-84dc-ef3e655baf2d", "value": "Use for unspecified musical instruments."}
{"id": "b3eecc63-c08f-4fe8-b699-f11f92a86c52", "value": "Coiled substance, usually metal or plastic, used to absorb shocks or in timepieces since it can stretch and return to its original shape."}
{"id": "c6e79161-9ad6-4670-8d23-f7e17d37db46", "value": "Equipment enabling a horse to be ridden or driven, eg. saddles, bridles, harnesses, stirrups etc."}

{"id": "e78279bf-f689-424d-8315-d47b97862b94", "value": "Articles intended for personal adornment, usually to be strung on items of jewellery or sewn onto clothing. They may be made out of worked raw materials (eg. shells) or be manufactured goods, for example glass beads."}

{"id": "8fbc3656-f7e6-4d3e-aee8-386664fe84b8", "value": "Hard semi-translucent ceramic material made out of kaolin, quartz and feldspar which is biscuit fired at around 1000 degrees Celsius and glaze fired at around 1300 degrees Celsius."}
{"id": "ec119240-8560-4ce6-84bd-a37475171fc1", "value": "Instruments for determining position at sea, e.g. compasses, sextants."}
{"id": "af375578-140a-480b-88d8-79432cef2922", "value": "Items that have been through a manufacturing process. Use specific type where known."}

{"id": "03da3d48-b037-40e8-86ae-66565f1047bd", "value": "Any form of arms or ammunition whether from a formal organized military context or as a general cargo. Use specific terms - e.g. swords, bombs, where known; otherwise use this term primarily in contexts where the arms are unspecified or ancient."}
{"id": "e9827284-06da-4c5f-bd47-fd2efb08dc05", "value": "A malleable water repellant substance created by animals or as a coating to parts of plants."}
{"id": "4f4f6533-09ac-4536-ba04-574dbf590780", "value": "A herbaceous plant grown for its fibre and marijuana, a drug derivative. The fibres are used in the manufacture of rope."}
{"id": "d2d74385-5557-4f8d-bdf6-1e8da725700d", "value": "Animal skins, either raw or dressed which are used in the tanning industry to produce leather."}
{"id": "39e479d3-0586-4ce7-b568-378b15c9c83b", "value": "A mineral, Sodium Chloride, obtained by mining or the evaporation of brine used as a seasoning and for preserving food."}
{"id": "870925a5-309f-4c83-9ea9-834a984ce7c9", "value": "The stigmas of the crocus, Crocus sativus, used as a flavouring and for colouring food."}
{"id": "63ca32df-f42d-4d3c-b41f-c84d51c150e4", "value": "A pungent condiment manufactured from the dried berries of the plant Piper Nigrum. Use for cargoes of peppercorns or ground pepper."}
{"id": "1e424f77-0a6c-4b18-8ea4-ebb61102deac", "value": "Savoury ingredients, such as herbs, used to add flavour to food."}
{"id": "f1706622-13e4-4f6b-8608-be63f3ca6c96", "value": "Ore containing a high proportion of zinc."}

{"id": "80bbc2b4-3ffb-4c76-981f-a890cc46efda", "value": "Containers of cylindrical form, traditionally made of curved wooden staves bound together by hoops of metal. Also includes modern plastic and metal barrels."}
{"id": "8f8b9491-c83d-4016-a4c3-2f56b7fd6e85", "value": "Wooden boxes or cases for carrying fruit and other similar goods."}
{"id": "3070902a-d8f6-4a67-a27a-2fdddf145c80", "value": "Coarse jute sacking"}

{"id": "6cf3192d-2ece-45c0-b1c2-b76269248b2f", "value": "Double-handled storage jars characterised by a long neck and long body used as food and wine containers and for carrying such goods as cargo, found on shipwrecks from Classical antiquity (Greek/Roman)."}
{"id": "15592622-b74a-4ef3-9db8-da701d8f2160", "value": "A standardized rectangular steel container used for the transportation of goods by road rail and sea."}
{"id": "a99134a4-e4f6-43c7-83a7-1340281a9563", "value": "Narrow necked containers, originally of leather but now usually made of glass or plastic. Used for storing liquids."}
{"id": "d6faf385-9127-42e5-bc16-3c380d602dbd", "value": "Receptacles, including boxes, barrels etc., designed to contain something."}
{"id": "b773a412-96f2-48b6-9302-b6d2522de8ce", "value": "Use for cargoes which are not specified."}

{"id": "ca6e330a-11b7-4c7d-aa40-86a8086ad867", "value": "Baggage, plate, money, clothes and other personal belongings of all kinds. Use only where the vessel is a cargo vessel conveying the goods of a person of consequence, e.g. a noble or diplomat, rather than for a general passenger vessel."}
{"id": "27acafce-7570-43e5-a811-6aa5bbb90fee", "value": "General merchandise and saleable commodities. Use more specific type where known."}
{"id": "21bd4ce7-cc17-43ac-a922-5807fd11f573", "value": "Oil obtained from the liver of the cod, providing a rich source of vitamins A and D."}
{"id": "bca042ee-82ad-41c2-8994-6e3ed9e58857", "value": "Coal dust or slack, especially that of anthracite."}
{"id": "3d53793f-6808-4079-8e43-8e3df8833b27", "value": "A light, buoyant material obtained from the cork oak. Cork is used in floats and as stoppers for bottles."}
{"id": "ed28105b-ba98-4ec5-87b6-02b9b4200135", "value": "Seed of the cotton plant from which edible oil is extracted."}
{"id": "bcd31e34-356a-491c-94a5-c650497d9c4a", "value": "A powder made from charcoal, sulphur and potassium nitrate and used as an explosive in fireworks, flintlock guns etc."}
{"id": "6ade44e0-3d26-45d7-9d60-1e8bb0925ea6", "value": "A high explosive, manufactured by absorbing unstable nitroglycerine in a material such as kieselguhr, a soft, earthy material."}

{"id": "7055d1b2-2cde-44bc-8366-cbd0127bdcd5", "value": "Containers filled with high explosive, which can be fired from artillery pieces, thrown, dropped by aircraft or placed by hand and detonated in various ways."}
{"id": "d13e45bb-80af-409d-ab68-b40d255f8c2c", "value": "Cylindrical, self-propelled missiles which travel underwater and explode on impact."}
{"id": "259c4ce5-eef8-4bc5-92ad-6cbd0ea188cb", "value": "Manufactured goods, including shells, dynamite etc., containing substances which can be made to explode."}
{"id": "e1dfbdbc-9f54-48fb-8916-f3665a815205", "value": "Explosive devices, usually of metal, placed in the ground or floating in water with the purpose of endangering enemy personnel or shipping."}
{"id": "fad6d94f-3282-4df6-85d8-80bf2da6e3a0", "value": "Bed coverings, usually of woollen or similar natural or artificial fabrics."}
{"id": "3e55c77e-4cfa-4f9a-b5d5-e8a3fea63b16", "value": "Woven or felted fabric used in the manufacture of garments, tablecloths, towels etc."}

{"id": "15a37a1a-48e5-4da4-a861-b3872d34503e", "value": "A strong unbleached cloth manuifactured from hemp, flax or similarly coarse yarn. Used mainly in the manufacture of sails, tents and for painting on."}
{"id": "c08709f0-06b3-4c89-b677-b912d61599f0", "value": "Wool, textile, or synthetic floor covering material."}
{"id": "149c8049-7fed-4504-b765-68a668037eff", "value": "Plain, white, cotton cloth often unbleached."}
{"id": "20631276-5c7a-4470-b741-0292c941e156", "value": "Threads of material used to form cloth."}
{"id": "b374c3ad-1e97-4105-a45c-12173669c8b6", "value": "The hair from the coat of goats and sheep, made into yarn and used in the manufacture of woollen cloth."}
{"id": "31a5d63e-4d69-4050-939b-c36bb786b5a2", "value": "Fabric manufactured from fibrous materials, consolidated by heat and compression so that the fibres become matted together."}
{"id": "0e5fdae3-f57f-449e-9e7b-c81ba7a4db0e", "value": "A cloth woven from flax."}
{"id": "f27616b7-02d8-45d5-945d-16eba51b6c3b", "value": "Canvas or similar fabric used for the manufacture of sails."}
{"id": "6decc788-a79c-476a-8633-df93c1d4af1f", "value": "A fine, soft fibre produced by silkworms and used to make thread for textiles. Also the cloth made from this thread."}

{"id": "2a7bc647-1abf-404f-8d80-e12c00581602", "value": "Pieces of material, usually decorated, used as standards, for signalling or for decoration. Often used as a symbol of a particular nation eg. the Union Flag of Great Britain."}

{"id": "af4602a6-4cf9-49b2-aa15-def22f201280", "value": "The white, fibrous substance surrounding the seeds of plants of the genus Gossypium, which can be spun and used in the manufacture of thread and cloth or used in its raw form as wadding or packing."}
{"id": "355ff446-5bc9-44b8-91cc-885cf44c6aaa", "value": "A living thing that is not an animal. Use for unspecified plants only. Use a more specific type where known."}
{"id": "4b429d3f-d734-49ec-bf86-5a256db670c6", "value": "Includes all trees, flowers, vegetables etc. and any products manufactured from them."}
{"id": "643a0d06-fb9f-4eb2-9460-5cc19ae48ee1", "value": "Products manufactured from plant materials."}
{"id": "623ee51c-5859-4a57-afd5-6d8737f6fce0", "value": "Wood, cut and seasoned for use as a constructional material."}
{"id": "12b3bdcb-667b-4786-9a1b-99db65452fbd", "value": "Traditionally, pieces of unleavened cake or bread usually small in size and dry, crisp and hard."}
{"id": "3cf1c0e0-eebb-4ec7-a5e4-8e42e15ca1f1", "value": "A fluid substance. Use for unspecified liquids only, where known use more specific type."}
{"id": "5630d439-8d1d-4c3f-941a-7455d41e13fc", "value": "A staple foodstuff made with flour, water and usually yeast, which is kneaded and then baked. Can include unleavened (no yeast) varieties."}
{"id": "f0ffdfe0-0ded-4cd2-90e6-830a44f4b8d3", "value": "Any of a large group of cold blooded vertebrates who live exclusively in water. Also can refer to the flesh of fish which is eaten."}
{"id": "4cb24076-0445-404e-a52f-ebae4b1af02f", "value": "Various flavoured aromatic and savoury substances, such as herbs, salt etc, used to impart flavour to food."}
{"id": "3c423703-5381-4636-85e5-5d2f3d98f2f3", "value": "Paste or cake of the fruit of the cacao-tree, sweetened with other substances and used to make beverages or confectionery."}
{"id": "0a4e53fc-c19f-4394-8570-a4648864c3e7", "value": "The edible seed of the palm tree."}
{"id": "c8bb76de-60d9-4163-9836-235095ae6624", "value": "Any plants which are grown to be eaten. Includes parts of plants, especially roots and leaves."}
{"id": "40dc037e-5895-4da0-9210-b82136bb222c", "value": "Includes raw and processed."}
{"id": "c53c4fc8-8fde-43e4-b1de-14c81ff51551", "value": "Products, such as cheese and butter, manufactured from milk."}
{"id": "011a0663-19c2-4f1f-9d22-d7ae4f0a8efc", "value": "Conelike spikes of the hop plant used in the brewing industry to give a bitter flavour to beer and malt liquors."}
{"id": "3de97f63-6594-49ac-8489-a67385e03a6c", "value": "Dried leaves from the plant Camellia sinensis, which is used to make a drink by infusing the leaves in boiling water."}
{"id": "83a94000-57a2-4e82-a122-35f60c5661cd", "value": "The flesh of animals, either raw or cooked, used as food."}
{"id": "774d162e-c83c-49d1-b2c6-93e9e91adf18", "value": "A sweet, crystalline subtance obtained from sugar beet or sugar cane and used in cooking, brewing etc."}
{"id": "376de1c1-807a-419a-bf1d-432063f8d145", "value": "Goods, usually foodstuffs, which have been sealed inside canisters, usually made of tin or steel, to preserve them."}
{"id": "dd763a41-f06a-4d21-8640-815fdff7669c", "value": "A pure starch obtained from the tubers of the plant Maranta arundinacea used in cookery as a thickening agent."}

{"id": "fa748062-8dbe-4e14-88ec-2f998c6f3996", "value": "A preparation made from the evaporated juice of the rhizome of the plant Glycyrrhiza glabra, used medicinally and as a sweet, usually in the form of a black, chewy substance."}
{"id": "7071d5e9-5fb9-4275-a860-84a8919493f7", "value": "Goods, usually foodstuffs, preserved in glass bottles, jars, etc. Examples are bottled fruit, pickled onions, jam, honey."}

{"id": "73325154-85a6-4e45-acce-f7de7ee61145", "value": "Traditionally any food preserved by boiling with sugar, salting, pickling etc. Nowadays used specifically for fruit which has been preserved with sugar."}
{"id": "81eb149b-9fff-491f-8e4c-ec75e169a41e", "value": "Fish eggs, e.g. from cod or, for example, caviar."}
{"id": "c12565bc-3495-4be7-8572-99dcd59c43c0", "value": "The beans, or powder resulting from grinding the beans, of shrubs of the genus Coffea. The powder is used to make the drink Coffee."}
{"id": "3bfaee44-4960-4cdc-817f-7c7983b42ad6", "value": "The edible product of a plant, usually consisting of the seed and its sweet, juicy envelope."}
{"id": "ec419746-45c2-49f8-8b62-64d5270620b4", "value": "Any of the plants of the grass family, Graminae, cultivated for their edible seeds, especially corn, wheat etc."}
{"id": "76d7f263-e8b9-48f7-9f6e-2da1a1605b19", "value": "Powder produced by grinding cacao beans, used as the main ingredient for the drink Cocoa."}
{"id": "3a570dba-bac4-4cc3-a4f2-a31e3955d53b", "value": "Cattle fodder or fertilizer resulting from the extracting of oil from seeds."}

{"id": "1359206e-2864-42a2-82ac-0ab9607c9c03", "value": "Shaped material used for covering buildings, usually as a roofing material though can be used on walls or floors. Often of fired clay they can be of other materials particularly stone."}
{"id": "26361211-d8e0-4cb7-9c79-fc3a6e5b47e1", "value": "Planks or boards manufactured from softwood timber."}
{"id": "c3eb3a6e-7a19-4048-ac35-6b6b1c049bdd", "value": "Metal spikes used for fixing one object to another."}
{"id": "b63f8619-7b38-44a8-9d2d-4a1fc27e637b", "value": "Pieces of timber shaped for use in the construction of buildings, barrels etc."}
{"id": "349d2fea-44bc-4aec-8264-00137b903320", "value": "Steel in the form of rails eg. for use in the construction of railways."}
{"id": "0e2c782a-7e17-47f0-a90d-f16f4248a11b", "value": "Poles of timber, metal etc. used as masts, booms or yards on a vessel."}

{"id": "aa2a2b0d-b84b-45cd-a6d7-9d73917cc34d", "value": "Hard, transparent, brittle substance manufactured by fusing soda or potash with other ingredients. Used for glazing windows and in the manufacture of drinking vessels."}
{"id": "ab865dcd-8dc1-414e-85b9-28fdc6286fbe", "value": "A long thin piece of wood,"}
{"id": "05c07eb1-f404-4839-bde2-36e1fbda48d8", "value": "Thin, rectangular tiles, usually made of wood, used for roofing."}
{"id": "5539b5a3-9b47-4215-9625-718c8806ca59", "value": "Iron in the form of rails eg. for use in the construction of railways."}
{"id": "1d107917-e7ba-401b-95b8-b794e9db3b7e", "value": "A liquid derived from wood tar through a distillation process. Now used to describe timber preservative derived from coal tar."}
{"id": "06f51b9a-2784-4184-a9f5-31639004ccb5", "value": "Fertile soil composed mainly of humus, sand and clay."}
{"id": "a4f960d5-74a5-47b7-b583-f45879550f71", "value": "Timber sawn into long, flat, pieces used for flooring etc. in buildings."}
{"id": "b822aeeb-69f2-4d1e-89e5-71740f6d0ed2", "value": "Flat, rectangular piece of material, traditionally of wood but now of any material, used in the construction industries."}
{"id": "58d8281d-a352-4ca2-acdb-7d0e8a9393ef", "value": "Bricks capable of withstanding heat without burning. Used to line fireplaces, kilns etc."}
{"id": "bc3a8d05-3f6b-4df7-a501-a02d8a3d9f71", "value": "A viscous, bituminous pitch which can be used for surfacing roads."}
{"id": "6d003b25-fe9e-4566-80cd-085e2d84d25f", "value": "Sheets of iron or steel bent into a series of ridges and hollows to give added strength and rigidity."}
{"id": "2a1d2b71-5939-4305-96ed-bd827d5f9054", "value": "Narrow strips of wood used in the building industry."}
{"id": "ea794f45-4ab4-4687-a533-6bbef1df9191", "value": "Beams of wood, iron, steel etc., used in the construction industry."}
{"id": "29e4b248-0d40-43ab-94b7-fc80a688b163", "value": "Construction blocks manufactured using clay which is then fired or sun dried."}
{"id": "235c4c94-7b81-497a-ae50-e8d14c88bb63", "value": "Materials used for the construction of buildings, vehicles or other objects."}
{"id": "750b3e1a-3302-4fed-a535-0276d85e7e18", "value": "Long narrow pieces of wood used for a variety of purposes."}
{"id": "ef3a98f1-90fa-4f2e-a8b0-455d9b2eb61a", "value": "Building material made by combining gravel, cement, water and sand. When hard it forms a stonelike surface, used for paving and building."}
{"id": "87f807b9-46eb-4949-8c46-e0faed597979", "value": "Hard wood, reddish-brown in colour with a fine-grain often used in the manufacture of furniture."}
{"id": "e7f8ad26-3148-40ec-9c57-bde8eb4736d8", "value": "Usually slag, a residue from burning stone, but can be used for vitrified bricks."}
{"id": "480d7c1b-a68f-45f3-8a6b-84909b6b9b7d", "value": "Fruit native to the countries bordering the Mediterranean Sea."}
{"id": "dd921a68-f311-4693-bd8a-02c3161cadf6", "value": "Silver fashioned into coin for use as currency."}
{"id": "7af0c1c4-e2e5-4e8f-985b-8902f1640210", "value": "An oil obtained by the distillation of wood and used as a solvent and paint thinner and in some medical preparations."}
{"id": "b7d6755a-016a-46ea-b44a-8c6a9ae577af", "value": "A heavy, metallic element, which is liquid at room temperature. Used in thermometers and medicinal preparations."}
